-- Bangladesh’s Inflation Slows to 8.03% in July, Official Says
-- B y   A r u n   D e v n a t h
-- 2012-08-05T10:36:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-05/bangladesh-s-inflation-slows-to-8-03-in-july-official-says.html
Bangladesh’s annual inflation rate
slowed to 8.03 percent last month from 8.56 percent in June,
Golam Mostafa Kamal, director general of  Bangladesh Bureau of
Statistics , said today.  Food inflation was 6.3 percent in July, compared with 7.08
percent in June, Kamal told reporters in Dhaka. Non-food
inflation decelerated to 11.54 percent from 11.72 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Arun Devnath in Dhaka at 
